KRIM_ROLE_T.DESC_TXT: This role derives its members from the users in the Principal table. This role gives users high-level permissions to interact with RICE documents and to login to KUALI.
This role derives its members from users with that have received an action request for a given document.
This role derives its members from the initiator listed within the route log of a given document.
This role derives its members from the initiator and action request recipients listed within the route log of a given document.
This role can take superuser actions and blanket approve RICE documents as well as being able to modify and assign permissions, responsibilities and roles belonging to the KR namespaces.
This role derives its members from users with the Edit Document permission for a given document type.,
This role derives its members from the user who took the Complete action on a given document.
This role derives its members from users with the Open Document permission for a given document type.,
This role derives its members from users with an acknowledge action request in the route log of a given document.
This role derives its members from users with an FYI action request in the route log of a given document.
This role represents the KR System User, that is the user ID RICE uses when it takes programmed actions.
This role derives its members from users with the Initiate Document permission for a given document type.
This role derives its members from users with an Approval action request (that was not generated via the ad-hoc recipients tab) in the route log of a given document.
This role maintains KRMS agendas and rules.
This role derives its members from users with the Route Document permission for a given document type.
This role is used for no login guest users.
This role derives its members from users with an complete action request in the route log of a given document.
